- (ChatGPT) "List 15 quotations about dealing with grief."
ChatGPT
Here are 15 quotations about dealing with grief, drawn from a mix of authors, thinkers, and artists who’ve touched on the pain and process of loss:

---

1. **“Grief is the price we pay for love.”**  
— *Queen Elizabeth II*

2. **“The reality is that you will grieve forever. You will not ‘get over’ the loss of a loved one; you will learn to live with it.”**  
— *Elisabeth Kübler-Ross and David Kessler*

3. **“What we have once enjoyed deeply we can never lose. All that we love deeply becomes a part of us.”**  
— *Helen Keller*

4. **“Give sorrow words; the grief that does not speak knits up the o’er-wrought heart and bids it break.”**  
— *William Shakespeare, *Macbeth*

5. **“Grief is like the ocean; it comes on waves ebbing and flowing. Sometimes the water is calm, and sometimes it is overwhelming.”**  
— *Vicki Harrison*

6. **“No one ever told me that grief felt so like fear.”**  
— *C.S. Lewis, *A Grief Observed*

7. **“You will lose someone you can’t live without, and your heart will be badly broken... And the bad news is that you never completely get over the loss of your beloved. But this is also the good news.”**  
— *Anne Lamott*

8. **“Tears shed for another person are not a sign of weakness. They are a sign of a pure heart.”**  
— *José N. Harris*

9. **“The deeper that sorrow carves into your being, the more joy you can contain.”**  
— *Kahlil Gibran, *The Prophet*

10. **“To weep is to make less the depth of grief.”**  
— *William Shakespeare, *Henry VI, Part 3*

11. **“Sometimes, only one person is missing, and the whole world seems depopulated.”**  
— *Alphonse de Lamartine*

12. **“Grief, I’ve learned, is really just love. It’s all the love you want to give but cannot.”**  
— *Jamie Anderson*

13. **“The pain of grief is just as much a part of life as the joy of love.”**  
— *Dr. Colin Murray Parkes*

14. **“There is a sacredness in tears. They are not the mark of weakness, but of power.”**  
— *Washington Irving*

15. **“It’s so much darker when a light goes out than it would have been if it had never shone.”**  
— *John Steinbeck*

---

Would you like these focused more on healing, remembrance, or acceptance? I can tailor more to a theme.